borrow(address,uint256,uint256).details: Lends to a wallet for a certain maturity date/pool

params.amount: amount to send to the specified wallet

getAccountSnapshot(address,uint256).details: Gets current snapshot for a wallet in a certain maturity

params.who: wallet to return status snapshot in the specified maturity date

getTotalBorrows(uint256).details: Gets the total amount of borrowed money for a maturityDate

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

rateForSupply(uint256,uint256).details: Rate that the protocol will pay when borrowing from an address a certain amount at the end of the maturity date

params.amount: amount to calculate how it would affect the pool
params.maturityDate: maturity date to calculate the pool

rateToBorrow(uint256,uint256).details: Rate that the protocol will collect when lending to an address a certain amount at the end of the maturity date

params.amount: amount to calculate how it would affect the pool
params.maturityDate: maturity date to calculate the pool

redeem(address,uint256,uint256).details: The pool that the user is trying to retrieve the money should be matured

params.maturityDate: the date to calculate the pool id
params.redeemAmount: The number of underlying tokens to receive from redeeming this Exafin (only one of redeemTokensIn or redeemAmountIn may be non-zero)
params.redeemer: The address of the account which is redeeming the tokens

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

repay(address,uint256,uint256).details: The pool that the user is trying to repay to should be matured

params.borrower: The address of the account that has the debt
params.repayAmount: the amount of debt of the underlying token to be paid

supply(address,uint256,uint256).details: Borrows from a wallet for a certain maturity date/pool

params.amount: amount to receive from the specified wallet

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

redeem(address,uint256,uint256).notice: User redeems (TODO: voucher NFT) in exchange for the underlying asset

repay(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Someone pays borrower's debt (can be borrower)
